{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexProtocol"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"StaticMutexProtocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"PointerWrapper","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PointerWrapperP"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Prior to GLib 2.32, GStaticMutex had the significant advantage"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that it doesn’t need to be created at run-time, but can be defined","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"at compile-time. Since 2.32, "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","isActive":true},{"text":" can be statically allocated","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"as well, and GStaticMutex has been deprecated."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Here is a version of our ","type":"text"},{"code":"give_me_next_number()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" example using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a GStaticMutex:"}]},{"code":["  int","  give_me_next_number (void)","  {","    static int current_number = 0;","    int ret_val;","    static GStaticMutex mutex = G_STATIC_MUTEX_INIT;","","    g_static_mutex_lock (&mutex);","    ret_val = current_number = calc_next_number (current_number);","    g_static_mutex_unlock (&mutex);","","    return ret_val;","  }"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":null},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Sometimes you would like to dynamically create a mutex. If you don’t","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"want to require prior calling to ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_thread_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", because your code"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"should also be usable in non-threaded programs, you are not able to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_mutex_new()"},{"text":" and thus ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex"},{"text":", as that requires a prior call to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_thread_init()"},{"text":". In these cases you can also use a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It must be initialized with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_mutex_init()"},{"type":"text","text":" before using it"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and freed with with "},{"code":"g_static_mutex_free()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" when not needed anymore to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"free up any allocated resources."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Even though "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is not opaque, it should only be used with"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the following functions, as it is defined differently on different"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"platforms."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"All of the g_static_mutex_* functions apart from","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_static_mutex_get_mutex()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" can also be used even if "},{"code":"g_thread_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"has not yet been called. Then they do nothing, apart from","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_mutex_trylock()"},{"text":" which does nothing but returning ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All of the g_static_mutex_* functions are actually macros. Apart from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"taking their addresses, you can however use them as if they were"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"functions."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexProtocol","type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying ","type":"text"},{"code":"GStaticMutex","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Alternatively, use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" as a lighweight, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use.","type":"text"}]}]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"inheritsFrom","title":"Inherits From","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"],"kind":"relationships"},{"title":"Conforming Types","ide